DRAGONTRAP Lv 20 w PLANT
These colossal plants have a well-earned name: their maws are large
enough to engulf the limbs of an adult dragon. These are, however,
more often used to capture and digest animals and humanoids.
The only good news about these monstrosities is that they are deeply
rooted in the ground — you can run away from them, assuming you
escape their lethal vines.
Typical Traits: colossal, hungry, patient, rooted in place.
DEX d8 INS d8 MIG d10 WLP d8 HP 90 w 45 MP 60 Init. 8
DEF +0 M.DEF +0 ' a RS b VUa E VU f RS i l RS b VU
BASIC ATTACKS
$ Dragoneater w【 MIG + MIG】 +5 w【 HR + 10】 physical damage. If a target hit by this attack
is weak, they are swallowed by the dragontrap: a swallowed creature will suffer minor (20)
physical damage at the beginning of each of the dragontrap's turns and can perform no
actions except for Objective (with the goal of freeing themselves).
Freeing a swallowed target is a four-section Clock; a soldier dragontrap can only have one
creature swallowed at the same time, but an elite or champion dragontrap can hold up to
two creatures in its maws at a time. If a dragontrap has all mouths occupied and swallows a
creature, it must also release one of the creatures it had previously swallowed.
a Lashing Vines w【 DEX + MIG】 +5 w【 HR + 15】 air damage and the target suffers weak.
SPELLS
h Numbing Gas r w【 MIG + WLP】 +2 w 10 × T MP w Up to three creatures w Instantaneous.
Each target loses half of their current Mind Points.
h Pre-digestion r w【 MIG + WLP】 +2 w 10 MP w One creature w Scene.
Until this spell ends, the target suffers 10 extra damage from all sources that deal physical
damage.
SPECIAL RULES
Plant w The dragontrap is immune to dazed, enraged, and shaken.
